VA scintillating performance
p3
sVnews
p4
VSouth Indian Cultural Association (SICA) recently organised a concert by Pantula Rama, from Vishakapatnam, as a part of Shanta Devi Memorial Concert. Rama was accompanied by her husband M.S.N. Murty, a leading AIR artiste, Nemani Somayajulu on mridangam and Shyam Kumar on the kanjeera.Rama, singing for the first time for SICA, gave a scintillating recital and enthralled therasikas. She began her recital with a lovely Sreeragam varnamwith a classy touch. Khambhoji was next to come forEkadantam Bhajehamof Deekshitar in Misra-chapu with crispswaramin it. Kalavathi, a rareragamwas neatly and  effectively sung forEnnadu Jhoothumoof Thyagaaraja. Rama also brought in the Hindustani touch in theragam.swaramwas the highlight.
